<text>
<body>

<div1 type="letter">
<pb facs="wfc.css00124.001" />

<opener>
<note type="letterhead">
<figure n="drawing"></figure>
The New<lb/>
Hoffman House,<lb/>
Madison Square,<lb/>
J. P. Caddagan, Manager.<lb/>
Absolutely Fire Proof.</note> 

<dateline>New York, <date>Mar. 23 1902</date></dateline>

<salute>My Dear <persName key="woods.a">Mr Wood</persName>&#8212;</salute>
</opener>

<p>Am glad that the bids begin to look more reasonable.<ref target="n01">1</ref> I would like to see the first story built of those different colored cobble stone. on the two front sides of the hotel the second of grey stone <choice><sic>trimed</sic><corr>trimmed</corr></choice> with red&#8212; she would then be a house that would get talked about&#8212;</p>

<closer>
<salute>Yours truly</salute>

<signed>W. F. Cody</signed>
</closer>
</div1>

<div1 type="envelope">

<pb facs="wfc.css00124.002" />

<note type="letterhead"><figure n="photographs"><figDesc>[Images of Cody and Salsbury]</figDesc></figure>Buffalo Bill's Wild West and Congress of Rough Riders of the World.<lb/>
Col. W. F. Cody. (Buffalo Bill) President.<lb/>
Nate Salsbury. Vice President &amp; Manager.<lb/>
Maj. Hon M. Burke Genl. Mgr. Jule Keen Bus. Mgr &amp; Treas.</note>

<ab type="postmark">Madison.Sq.Sta.-N.Y. 1902 Mar 23  5&#8212;PM</ab>

<figure n="stamp"><figDesc>[Postage stamp, rotated counterclockwise, red]</figDesc> <p>United State Postage 2 two cents 2</p></figure>


<ab type="address">

<address>
<addrLine>A. W. Wood</addrLine>
<addrLine>Architect</addrLine>
<addrLine>Lincoln</addrLine>
<addrLine>Neb</addrLine>
</address>

</ab>
</div1>


</body>

<back>
<note xml:id="n01">Note 1: Cody probably refers to cost estimates for the <orgName key="hotel.i">Irma Hotel</orgName>.</note>
</back>
</text>
